"The Facebook excludes all of this - you're addressing them directly."
Others say that this site could identify and explore social health problems.
A recent study by Dr. Megan Moreno of the University of Wisconsin, Madison, and her colleagues showed that students who discussed their drinking promotions in Facebook were significantly more at risk of alcoholism than those who were silent about it.
Moreno assumes that students' peers, such as their community teachers, could monitor the site and interfere to help a student who is too often updating his drinking status.
