"We've found a way to identify children from a risk group they wouldn't find otherwise."
Facebook is also constantly collecting data about its users.
The Data Processing Unit processed statistics on relations and Valentine's Day, the occurrence of voters in mid-2010 as well as the National Happiness Index (mostly using the information available to them, the cyberfreedom champions have long insisted that the site should make its extensive collection of data available to the public for research).
